Java Multithreading Assignment Answers 
1. What is Multithreading and why is it important? 
Multithreading is the ability of a CPU to execute multiple threads concurrently within a single process. 

• Importance: It allows for maximum utilization of the CPU. By performing multiple tasks simultaneously, 
it keeps the CPU busy and prevents idle time during I/O operations. 

2. Benefits of Multithreading 
• Improved Performance: Better resource utilization leads to faster execution. 
• Responsiveness: Keeps applications (like GUIs) responsive while background tasks run. 
• Parallelism: Tasks can run truly simultaneously on multi-core systems. 
• Resource Sharing: Threads share the same memory space, making communication efficient. 

